> In our humble opinion, flatbreads > pizza, any day! We know that may sound blasphemous, but stick with us. First of all, the golden, crispy crust is a veritable blank canvas. It's not beholden to simply marinara and mozz! In fact, ours is topped with a creamy garlic sauce, savory chicken sausage, roasted tomato and onion, and melty mozz. Can your 'za do that?! Yeah, we didn't think so.

== Roast Veggies and Garlic ==

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Line a #baking sheet{} with foil. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and cut @yellow onion{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Cut @Roma tomato{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Peel @garlic{1%clove} and place in the center of a small piece of foil; drizzle with @olive oil{1%tbsp} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cinch into a #packet{}.

Toss onion and tomato on prepared baking sheet with a drizzle of olive oil, half the @Italian seasoning{1%tbsp} (you'll use the rest later), salt, and pepper. Arrange tomato wedges skin sides down. Place foil packet with garlic on same sheet.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

== Cook Sausage ==

While veggies and garlic roast, heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @Italian chicken sausage mix{9%ounce} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

== Toast Flatbreads ==

Once veggies and garlic are done, transfer to a plate. Carefully discard foil lining and packet. Wipe off any excess oil from baking sheet.

Place @flatbreads{2} on same sheet and return to top rack until lightly toasted, ~{5-7%minutes}. (For 4 servings, divide between 2 sheets and toast on top and middle racks; swap rack positions halfway through toasting.)

== Make Garlic Sauce ==

While flatbreads toast, transfer roasted garlic to a #cutting board{}; roughly chop or mash with a fork.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in pan used for sausage over medium-high heat. Add @flour{1%tbsp} and remaining Italian seasoning. Whisk constantly until lightly browned, ~{30%seconds}.

Reduce heat to medium low and whisk in @cream cheese{4%tbsp}, garlic, and @water{1/2%cup} (1 cup for 4) until combined. Simmer until just thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: If sauce is too thick, add more water a splash at a time.

== Assemble and Broil ==

Heat broiler to high. Evenly spread flatbreads with sauce, then top with sausage, tomato, and as much onion as you like. Sprinkle with @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}.

Broil flatbreads until cheese melts, ~{1-2%minutes}. (For 4 servings, broil in batches.)

> TIP: Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Cut flatbreads into pieces, divide between plates, and serve.